<p class="">This, if it is true, is being inflicted with their complete agreement, which is, I am informed, the greatest body of agreement ever reached between a Minister and representatives of the local authorities' associations. My Department could well have maintained that we ought to have deducted £100—perhaps even more; but we have agreed, and they have accepted—as, I think, a generous settlement—a reduction of £50 from what would have been the cost of the notional standard average house calculated on the old system.</p>                    <div class="hidden-md hidden-lg" style="padding-left: 0px;">
