<p class="">I am quoting the interest rates; the difference over 60 years on 3 per cent. and 4¼ per cent. Surely I have made my point. It is a difference of over £1,000 per house. I was quoting a £1,600 house and that if the hon. Member works it out, he will find that I am correct. It does not mean that it costs £2,600 at once; it is over the long period of a 60-year loan.</p>                    <div class="hidden-md hidden-lg" style="padding-left: 0px;">
