<p class="">The hon. Gentleman says that I misled the House. That is absolutely untrue. I applied exactly the same process of calculation as has always been applied. Of course, some houses cost less and some more. In fixing the subsidy, we always base ourselves on the average and, broadly speaking, any increase of burden which comes along from the increase in the rate of interest is met by the housing subsidy.</p>                    <div class="hidden-md hidden-lg" style="padding-left: 0px;">
