<p class="">I only have time to shoot off a few of the facts with which I have armed myself. The right hon. Gentleman has already intervened a great deal, as well as making a long speech.<p></p> I should now like to deal with the question of the sale of council houses. The hon. Member for Lincoln who opened for the Opposition referred to this part of the Bill as "rank Toryism."</p>                    <div class="hidden-md hidden-lg" style="padding-left: 0px;">
